\f11\i \cf0 Once upon a time, a land far far away in a place beyond time called here. A little being with a puny little lizard brain, actually, well, technically...Wilder was his name.\
Wilder was a dreamer, but that's what they loved him as. No, Wilder was a believer, but that's what they only knew to call him as. See, Wilder was a Knowar. Something different about his little lizard brain, a mutation perhaps, of perhaps simply the Wilder-ness had got him. Wilder knowars thing because he sees them first hand when he goes there and does there. Anywhere really...which to those less inclined with the art of knowing, this was simply terrifying...so Wilder found himself, exiled in the Wilder-ness, the place where by definition, only the inconceivable may survive and thrive, but only if they do. If do not, the beasts and terrors lurk...monsterous creatures...\
But Wilder was a knowar. And Wilder knew he just needed to find the right way to fit in, for he loved the wilder-ness, his home, so one day after fearing and struggling so long, Wilder simply decided it was time to just be the Knowar he is, trust in his abilities, and _just say 'HI'_ to people, and make _friends_ and _familiy_...to find his Wilder-ness people. So he let his vision lead him through the day, faith. He let his vision be his sight, and when he did, the pitch blackness of the Wilder-ness just _illuminated_, so he wandered with the aim of knowar vision of his nose.\
And one day, Wilder peering through a bush concealed, saw a vast beast that he had always heard to keep away from...the nonknow sight of those others they call hearing as believing, he say it had _legs_! ...The others that exiled him, they told tales of a _snake_. The Knowar he was, he took a moment and absorbed the suspense...it filled his little lizard brain with knowarings that told a story, a beautiful story, a terrifying--knowar terrific rather--beast like a HeRecksSoreUs Groks!, but he was clearly plenty well fed, beautiful, majestic in his massive stature, more like tyrannasaurus Roks!, the brain of that beast, surely knowar too...\
*snap!* Wilder accidentally cracked a twig! Wilder gave away his cover to the beast!! DANGER!! But knowar happened semi-colon vector, so Wilder did not flee, he let his vision be his brain, be bigger than it be. And he invented on the spot, a story, but nobody likes strangers forcing stories, so he invented it a game...for if the beast was likewise knowar, then he knew the beast was almost certainly alone in the wilder-ness for similar reasons as Wilder. And it clicked! Wilder thought...'Its not a game as a trick! ...its a game as an invitation to tell our story together, as friends, because playing games with friends is fun! The story is the trick! ...but the trick is transparent! ...the story is the secret hid plain sight! All I have to do, is let my knowar seeing, see the truth...from my side and his...and if I let my knowar follow my soul...may be he will see what I see...that we are the same.\
So Wilder didn't flee or freeze, but he leveraged restraint to harness the momentum of that crack in bush moment, and he fed it, and rustled and shook it, making sure that the beast knew of his presence, but not an ambush...and then he softened this third derivative jerksss, and emerged smoothly, by this time, with the perfect 'hello' held in ready, to let out...
